  "text": "The precise role of the calcium current in the embryonic cockroach brain neurons in primary culture remains speculative. Under normal conditions (i.e., in cockroach saline), these neurons, similar to most insect neurons, have been shown to be electrically silent, partly because of the small size of the TTX-sensitive sodium current, and partly because of its very large delayed rectifier current (see [CITATION_1] .",
